fields.question: How can I purchase farm products through HarvestSaver Network?
fields.answer: To purchase farm products, simply browse our "Products" section, select the items you want, and add them to your cart. Proceed to checkout, where you can review your order, choose a delivery option, and make a secure payment.

fields.question: Are the farm products on HarvestSaver Network organic and locally sourced?
fields.answer: Yes, we prioritize offering organic and locally sourced farm products. Our platform connects you directly with farmers who adhere to sustainable and organic farming practices, ensuring fresh and high-quality produce.

fields.question: Can I contact the farmers directly to inquire about specific farm products?
fields.answer: Absolutely! We encourage communication between buyers and farmers. Each product listing includes contact information for the farmer. Feel free to reach out, ask questions, and establish a direct connection with the farmers.

fields.question: How do I list my equipment for rental on HarvestSaver Network?
fields.answer: To list your equipment for rental, navigate to the "Equipment" section and click on "List Your Equipment." Fill out the required details, including equipment specifications, rental rates, and availability. Once submitted, your equipment will be visible to potential renters.

fields.question: Can I request a specific piece of equipment for a future date?
fields.answer: Yes, you can! Navigate to the equipment listing you're interested in and check the availability calendar. If the equipment is available on your desired date, you can submit a reservation request. The owner will review your request and confirm availability.
